it/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Exponential.html#Real.exp\">Real.exp</a> (<span class=\"fn\">t</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">X</span> <span class=\"fn\">ω</span></span>)</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">t</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For `t : ℝ` with `t ∈ interior (integrableExpSet X μ)`, the derivative of the function\n`x ↦ μ[X ^ n * exp (x * X)]` at `t` is `μ[X ^ (n + 1) * exp (t * X)]`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Moments/MGFAnalytic.html#ProbabilityTheory.hasDerivAt_integral_pow_mul_exp_real","kind":"theorem","line":41,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.hasDerivAt_integral_pow_mul_exp_real","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Moments/MGFAnalytic.lean#L41-L56"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Probability.Moments.ComplexMGF","Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.Complex.Analytic","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.Taylor"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Probability.Moments.MGFAnalytic"}